ations. Protect, Serve, and Deport explains how local politics, state laws, institutional policies, and police practices work together to deliver immigrants into an expanding federal deportation system, conveying powerful messages about race, citizenship, and belonging.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aImmigration enforcementzTennesseezNashville. 0aLatin AmericanszTennesseezNashville. 0aNoncitizensxGovernment policyzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  acitizenship.  acriminals.  adeportation.  afederal deportation system.  aimmigration enforcement program.  aimmigration officers.  ainstitutional policies.  ajail employees.  ajail.  alatino residents.  alatinx.  alaw enforcement.  alocal immigration enforcement.  alocal police.  alocal politics.  aminor violations.  anashville.  apolice practices.  apolice.  arace.  aracism.  aremovable immigrants.  astate laws.  atennessee.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066755440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520968868?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968868zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520968868/original  a978-3-11-066755-4 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA